Version 0.1.3
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Removed %>>%, %<%, %<<%. The first is not needed anymore as %>% will only
match against dots at the "first level" call. It is a design decision to not
encourage deeper "nesting".

Also, when omitting parentheses, e.g. rnorm(100) %>% mean, the expression
is evaluated in the calling environment. Before this case was evaluated in the
operator's own scope.


Version 0.1.2
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Added the function

  add  (add columns to a data.frame and returns the new data.frame)


Version 0.1.1
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Added the function

  ofclass  (selects columns which has one of the specified classes)
  rows     (selects rows using numerical indices and/or amounts)



Version 0.1
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Initital version, which contains the main operators

  %>%, %<%, %>>%, %<<%.

and the convenience functions

  select   (selects, creates, or renames columns of data.frame)
  delete   (deletes columns from a data.frame)
  where    (filters a data.frame based on logical condition(s))
  orderby  (orders a data.frame)